<plot>Don and Phil Everly, whose hits included "Wake Up Little Susie", "Bird Dog" and "Cathy's Clown", hosted this summer replacement variety series for "The Johnny Cash Show". While most of the show's focus was on music--rock, gospel and country &amp; western--there were a few comedy sketches tossed into the mix as well.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?555875</url></doc>
